    <div class="quick-answer">
      <h2>The Short Answer</h2>
      <p>Here's what 150 grams of protein looks like in a day: <strong>3 eggs + Greek yogurt at breakfast (35g)</strong>, a large chicken breast at lunch (45g), cottage cheese mid-afternoon (25g), and ground beef or salmon at dinner (45g). Four eating occasions, real food, no extreme portions.</p>
