    <p>Here's what 150 grams of protein looks like in a day — and why it's the right target for men over 40 who have already built the 120–130g habit and want to push further without jumping straight to the more demanding 160g mark.</p>

    <p>150g sits in a specific zone: past maintenance, not yet full recomposition. For men training 3–4 times per week and trying to lose some fat while holding muscle, this is the number that starts to move the needle on body composition rather than just preventing loss.</p>

    <div class="killer-line">
      130g holds your ground.<br><span>150g is where you start taking it back.</span>
    </div>

